Small data regression

Load some packages

library(data.table)
library(caret)
library(caTools)

Problem statement

Let’s simulate a small data regression problem:

2,000 rows 500 columns 200 of the columns are actually noise 10% of the data is the positive class

nrows <- 2000
ncols <- 500
noise_vars <- 200
pct <- .50

Build the dataset

Simulate the data:

set.seed(42)
X <- matrix(rnorm(nrows*ncols*3), ncol=ncols)
CF <- runif(ncols, min=-1, max=1)
CF[sample(1:ncols, noise_vars)] <- 0
Y <- X %*% CF + rnorm(nrows, sd=10)

Split the classes:

cutoff <- quantile(Y, 1-pct)
Y <- as.integer(Y > cutoff)

Combine into one table:

dat <- data.table(Y=Y, X)

Create 2 training sets and ONE test set:

train_a <- dat[1:nrows,]
train_b <- dat[(nrows+1):(nrows*2),]
test <- dat[(nrows*2+1):(nrows*3),]

Fit models and predict on the test set

model_a <- glm(Y ~ ., train_a, family='binomial')
model_b <- glm(Y ~ ., train_b, family='binomial')

pred_a <- predict(model_a, test, type = 'response')
pred_b <- predict(model_b, test, type = 'response')

Compare results

100% mis-match at 6 decimal places:

sum(round(pred_a, 6) == round(pred_b, 6))
## [1] 0

Correllation between 2 models is low:

cor(pred_a, pred_b)
## [1] 0.5024911
summary(abs(pred_a - pred_b))
##      Min.   1st Qu.    Median      Mean   3rd Qu.      Max. 
## 0.0000007 0.0338400 0.1689000 0.2770000 0.4772000 0.9912000
plot(pred_a ~ pred_b)

In THEORY, these models should be identical, but in practice they are different, because the dataset is so small. The predicted probabilities differ by up to 99.1% between the 2 models, even though in theory they should be identical!
